Mzansi’s top socialite and influencer Sarah Langa has officially relocated to London. Langa, who was married to the controversial wealthy businessman Jehan Mackay for less than five years, took to Instagram to share her new life in an apartment in London. Shortly after her divorce, she was linked to Grammy award winner Black Coffee and recently to US rapper Meek Mill. The influencer, who first gained popularity on the Instagram platform, is popular for dripping in nothing but luxury and is fabulosity personified. A source close to Langa said she has secured a couple of job interviews and has been meeting with different potential brands to influence for them. “I feel like she has reached the ceiling here. The South African marketing sector, when it comes to social media, doesn’t have much to offer,” said the source. The source added that Langa doesn’t want to end up like other influencers, pushing brands she doesn’t want to, just to be affiliated with as if she is desperate for cash.  Hubby dumps influencer Langa  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.